title: Looks like it’s going to be Vitter vs. Bel Edwards in the Louisiana gubernatorial runoff… | Politics
text:
(Before It's News)
…if these Louisiana gubernatorial numbers from AoSHQ Decision Desk hold up . With 55% of the vote in Sen. David Vitter (R-LA) 84% is about fifteen thousand votes up on Scott Angele; the GOP/Dem breakdown of the vote looks to be about 60/40, with John Bel Edwards bringing in 38%. That’s… not going to be enough for an upset in the runoff, unless there’s a supernova of a revelation between now and Election Day. Still, there’s the possibility of an upset on the GOP side; keep watching the skies. Or just AoSHQ Decision Desk.
